The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques for target classification using GPR data. Specifically, it focuses on dictionary learning and sparse representation for feature extraction and classification. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical tests for parameter selection, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
